Johnny Edward Top Nigerian sprinter Enoch Adegoke has received N50,000  from the Ministry of Youth and Sports Development, The PUNCH reports. The money is part of the ministry’s efforts in helping athletes cushion the effect of the coronavirus pandemic. Adegoke, who holds a personal best of 10.12secs in 100m and 21.07secs in 200m, praised the Ministry of Youth and Sports Development for the gesture, adding that the fund will help him in numerous ways. “It’s true I got the palliative and I want to thank the ministry for the support, this will go a long way during this period, but I must state that I didn’t grumble initially as reported,” Adegoke told The PUNCH. Copyright PUNCH.
